.:: Puzzle 4x3-Level-3-8::.
There are 3 different favourite beverages: tea, juice, lemonade
City: edinburgh, marseilles, san-francisco
3 different pets are kept: frog, guinea-pig, mouse
The people use 3 different means of transport: bus, jet-ski, trike
1. the person traveling to san-francisco is the person driving the bus##1
2. the owner of the mouse is on the left of the person drinking juice##1
3. the person traveling to edinburgh is on the left or right of the person driving the jet-ski##3
4. the person drinking lemonade is on the left of the owner of the mouse##1
5. the person drinking lemonade is the person driving the trike##1
6. the person traveling to san-francisco is the owner of the frog##1

.:: Answer ::.
|             |      1      |     2     |      3      |
| Beverage       | lemonade | tea    | juice |
| City         | edinburgh   | marseilles | san-francisco     |
| Pet         | guinea-pig  | mouse     | frog        |
| Transport   | trike       | jet-ski   | bus         |

